The paper deals with feature selection, which is a common problem in machine learning and data mining. The focus is on high dimensional low sample size (HDLSS) data, which is a common scenario in computer vision, natural language processing, and other areas. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions experimental results on benchmark data sets, which suggests that it may belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.DM (Data Mining). Finally, the paper discusses the limitations of existing feature selection criteria, which may make it relevant to cs.ST (Statistics).
